<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-737-556  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 737 556.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  August 13 1990 v7 n32 p16(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Mac file server pairs motherboard with disk, tape. (Racet ComputesLtd.'s Mac-in-a-Box file server storage system) (Hardware)(product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Sullivan, Kristina B.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Racet Computes Ltd. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Racet Computes Mac-in-a-Box (File server) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionFile ServersStorage Equipment.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Kristina B. SullivanandM;BOSTON -- Racet Computes Ltd. expanded its role as a Macintosh storagesupplier last week by announcing a new file server that combines a MacintoshIIcx motherboard with disk and tape drives.andM;Called Mac-in-a-Box, the floor-mounted system includes the IIcx motherboard;a floppy-disk drive; up to six Racet 657M-byte hard-disk drives; and a2.2G-byte 8mm tape drive, a 525M-byte quarter-inch tape drive or a 600M-byterewritable optical drive for backup and archiving applications.andM;The new server also includes an Apple monitor, keyboard, video card andmouse, enabling the system to double as a high-performance CAD/CAM ordesktop-publishing workstation.andM;In addition, users can access up to 15.7G bytes of primary hard-disk storagespace with additional Racet Gigastor expansion cabinets.andM;&quot;Mac-in-a-Box is designed for use anyplace you would see a very largeMacintosh networking configuration where centralized storage and the abilityto manage backups is required,&quot; said Ron Johnston, vice president ofmarketing for Racet in Brea, Calif.andM;At the New York Daily News, for instance, a Mac-in-a-Box unit currentlyserves as the central processor for a Macintosh-based network, providing 2Gbytes of on-line hard-disk storage, according to Johnston.andM;Mac-in-a-Box units are priced between $2,995 and $4,995, depending onconfiguration.andP;  The system boasts data-access rates of 13.5 milliseconds andsupports AppleShare, A/UX and TOPS.andM;Racet Computes can be reached at (714) 579-1725.andO;</TEXT></DOC>